    "causal_summary": "The embed path strips the highest-value curated retrieval signal before it ever reaches a vector. `normalizeContentForEmbedding` at `content-normalizer.ts:216-231` strips the YAML frontmatter at line 222, strips anchors at line 223, and flattens every markdown heading to a plain label at line 228 via `normalizeHeadings`. The frontmatter `trigger_phrases` and `title` and the header path that the author curated are gone by the time the chunk is hashed and embedded, so a spec-doc chunk vector carries only its flattened body prose and none of its strongest intent signal.",
